The paper discusses deep learning and specifically dropout learning, which is a technique used to prevent overfitting in deep learning models. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) or neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper mentions visual object recognition and speech recognition, which are both applications of computer vision (cs.CV) and natural language processing (cs.CL), respectively. Finally, the paper discusses the process of combining neglected hidden units with the learned network, which can be seen as an ensemble learning technique. Therefore, the paper may also belong to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category.
